reviews.excerpt:
Me parece un local pésimo. Se equivocaron con el pedido (pedí una doble y me dieron una simple) y tras manosear mi hamburguesa metieron otro filete y me la devolvieron envuelta en papel como si fuese nueva. Tuve que exigir una hamburguesa nueva... pero me parece increíble que ni se molestaran en tirar algo que el dependiente de la caja había manoseado sin guantes. ¿Qué sanidad hay en este local?
Por otro lado, los baños estaban sucios (por poner un adjetivo). En el suelo había un charco de meados y había un olor fortísimo.
Desde luego no vuelvo.

When you leave to pay there are only 2 tills open for 40 people, if you want to use the lockers make sure to have the right coin in change or face a long queue at the customer info desk (why use lockers that take one coin type anyway, or why is any coin needed?!). reviews.excerpt:
It's in the Thai style of Siam park, and I couldn't find fault with it. There's something for everyone there and didn't see any of the over inflated prices of some of the other shipping centres. Definitely worth a visit.
 I've seen the stupid reviews based on the fact that a woman opened a box of perfume and started spraying it round when there's no tester? She got bent out of shape because perfume expensive and she's spraying it round like a can of lynx(axe) and it's probably worth €100+, 2* ???? Get over yourself! The mall is made up of over 50+ different stores over 2 stories, there's a kids area with a gymcana similar to go-ape in the UK and around 7 or so bars/resturants which are fantastic, while we were there there were teens belting out operatic classis on the stage and I'm told there are other bands playing here. Last but not least there's a hyper Dino supermarket on the floor above the underground parking which is far better value than anything else within 4-5km. Well worth a visit to the Lizarran for some tapas and beers, or Toni Roma for a Tex Mex/Americano
reviews.author: rob o'connor

reviews.excerpt:
Se aleja un poco a los restaurantes orientales tradicionales y más aún a los que ofrecen buffets. El servicio es ágil, se ordena en la mesa y los platos se piden de tres en tres.

La variedad del menú es muy amplia y las medidas de las porciones que traen los platos permiten que pruebes muchos más de los que normalmente pruebas en los buffets orientales. Recomiendo el pato crujiente y el arroz con pollo curry bok choy. Las sopas también están deliciosas.

Sorprende encontrarse un Parador con un aspecto tan moderno. Debido al mal tiempo que hizo todo el fin de semana en Cádiz, tuvimos que disfrutar de las instalaciones del hotel. 
Nos dieron una habitación en la última planta desde el que teníamos una magnifica vista al Parque Genovés. Las habitaciones eran muy amplias y repleta de detalles.
La única pega que puedo encontrarle es su restaurante, me decepcionó tanto la variedad como el sabor de lo elegido.
reviews.author: Diego Martín Fernández

reviews.excerpt:
Very expensive and the food is typical for early 1990:s cooking, we expected more from what guides call "cadiz' best restaurant". 
Great pata negra ham and gambas, but the fish dishes we had were underseasoned and overcooked. 
Also, the ambiance was very stiff, making the experience hard to enjoy. We were served some amuse bouches before the food came in, and without informing us, they later showed up on the bill. 
The whole restaurant is like a time capsule back to the 1980/90:s, which could be kind of charming but then it would also require perfect cooking.

reviews.excerpt: Classic restaurant, with classic dishes. Good quality, elegant place with elegant staff, warm and welcoming. All the food and drink is very reasonably priced also.
reviews.author: Richard Swinhoe

reviews.excerpt:
Did not realise it was a gay hangout until you see the flag. What I'm saying is that it's not in your face. Only realised after wondering why so many guys were at this end and saw the flag..penny dropped then. 

Have to stress it's not gay only hangout! So couples and families still very welcome. 
Music choice was a bit weird and got a bit annoying, but you soon learn to block that out as we returned 4 times during our holiday as it was so well priced and this side of the beach was less packed. 
9 euros for 1 parasol and 2 loungers which is reasonable for days use. The old gentleman who gave us tickets was lovely and kept and eye on everything.

Clean toilets and clean beach! 
Friendly staff 
Safe enough to leave our stuff hanging while we took a dip.
Welcoming and good choice of food and drinks which was reasonably priced.

ONLY Downside - sun is blocked due to building behind but this only happens around 6 or 7pm by which time you are ready to head for dinner away from the beach.
reviews.author: Thurka Singam

reviews.excerpt: Very clean beach. You can take a nice stroll. There are lots of souvenir shops and small restaurants along the way.

Recent changes are designed to get you to walk past more shops and spend more money than I'd really want to do but I guess it keeps the price of flights lower (yeah right).

Lo mejor el arroz meloso de pato y setas.

reviews.excerpt: Muy buena experiencia con el menu.  Cuenta con la posibilidad de pedir arroz y te lo hacen en el momento,  toda la mesa tiene que pedir el mismo pero por un precio de 15 euros ofrece unos exquisitos primeros y un buen arroz.  El postre y el cafe ni estan incluidos pero la calidad precuo es muy buena.
reviews.author: Roberto Gutierrez

reviews.excerpt: Lástima, un local tan original. Museo homenaje a las  motos y que cada  año su comida sea peor !!! Pero este año se lleva la palma!!!!! Hamburguesa de buey que no es de buey, a no ser que existe un buey que su carne sea de color blanco y su sabor a pollo/pavo. Su menú de arroz a banda. Podríamos decir... arroz con mini cangrejos y quenado. Desde luego no "asocarrat" la camarera de la terraza, muy mona pero nada organizada y bastante mal educada. Vamos que tres dias que hemos ido a comer solo se salva la pizza. Ya no lo recomiendo para nada!!!!
reviews.author: Kika Cuevas

reviews.excerpt: El bar es de ambiente motero varios menús de comidas y almuerzos, buenas vistas al mar. El problema es el parking de motos que hay enfrente dejan aparcar los coches y las motos vamos con 400 kg de moto subiendo bordillos y aparcando indebidamente en la acera,  creo que esto debería  controlarlo más la dirección y avisas a la policía de Los coches que ocupan las plazas de las motos,  a no ser que sean ellos los de los coches

reviews.excerpt:
La oferta del 7º arte en Valladolid está casi monopolizada por las grandes cadenas, pero hay que reconocer que la forma de que un cine funcione, es ofrecer salas de gran calidad (visual, sonora, temperatura, comodidad) y un gran abanico de películas y horarios.

En este caso CINESA es la operadora propietaria de, en mi humilde opinión, las mejores salas de cine en relación precio/calidad de Valladolid.

Está claro que lo ideal es ir el día del espectador (miércoles) o aprovechar las fechas puntuales de “la fiesta del cine", pero si como en mi caso, en días laborables lo tienes complicado... al menos en este cine podrás ver una película en fin de semana por poco más de 5€, utilizando la tarjeta de fidelización CINESA CARD (con la que además acumulas puntos, yo ya he tenido alguna entrada gratuita). Pero ojito con las palomitas porque como pidas el cubo grande y 2 refrescos grandes, pagarás más que por la película (13€).

El otro gran “pero" de estás salas de cine y las de otra gran centro comercial cercano a Valladolid, es que necesitas coche... Hay algún servicio especial de autobuses, pero desconozco los horarios.

En definitiva, unas salas de cine muy recomendables, si tienes coche y haces uso de la tarjeta CINESA CARD.
reviews.author: Rodrigo Martínez

reviews.excerpt:
Muy buen sonido y muy buena imagen. No sé si la mejor de Valladolid, pero en estos dos aspectos sólo en competencia con los de Río Shopping.
El precio de la entrada es exagerado, pero eso queda más o menos arreglado con la tarjeta de fidelización.
Lo que sigue siendo carísimo es comer palomitas y beber refresco comprados allí, a pesar del pequeño descuento que incluyen con la entrada.
Lo peor (aunque parece que lo están mejorando) son los 15 minutos de anuncios al estilo Antena 3 que meten antes de la peli; si fueran todo trailers de otras películas, ni tan mal, pero ver publicidad de coches, de detergentes, etc... Es mortal (pagar una pasta para ver la tele, vaya).
A pesar de todo siguen siendo mi elección habitual.

reviews.excerpt:
The food over here was excellent. The music and the decor really fits into the whole atmosphere. 

We ordered pakora and samosa for starters. To top it of, for mains we had a portion of Tiger prawns curry and a Sea food platter for 1, that also came with lamb and chicken. 

Words can't describe how amazing the food was. Highly recommended and would visit again. Just watch out how much you order, we barely made it to the hotel due to the size of the portions. Food is on the expensive side, but if you want to experience a good Indian cuisine highly recommended. 

We didn't make a reservation but we were still very welcome and they found seating for us immediately. All though, I would recommend calling if you do decide to come during the busy periods.

I almost forgot, don't forget to order the cheesy naan bread.

reviews.subj: Review from Cia. de dansa pumpàkatum
reviews.excerpt: Fatal, la peor experiencia que he tenido en un restaurante. Me sentí tan insultado que nos levantamos y nos fuimos sin llegar ni a pedir. Íbamos con un tiquet de descuento y la persona que nos atendió (parecía el encargado) fui extremadamente mal educado y grosero, como si quisiéramos estafarle: solo porqué le dije que no había podido reservar porqué cuando llamé a su número de teléfono me salió que no estaba operativo! Me dijo que estaba intentando tomarle el pelo. Perdón???!!! Simplemente iba a comer con amigos y a pasar un rato agradable! Luego me arrepentí de no haber pedido el libro de reclamaciones, pero en ese momento no quería ponerme (más ) de mala leche, sino encontrar otro lugar para donde sí quieran atender bien a sus clientes y olvidar la mala experiencia. A parte, el local aparece mucho más bonito en las fotos cuando en realidad no tiene ninguna gracia.
reviews.author: Cia. de dansa pumpàkatum

reviews.excerpt:

reviews.excerpt: Teníamos un descuento de Letsbonus. El trato poco simpático y las pizzas parecían chicle. De los postres que ponía en el tiquet, sólo coincidia uno. Nos hicieron pagar las bebidas: dos coca-colas, una cerveza y una agua por 10 € .....

reviews.excerpt: Mala experiencia en general. Comida infinitamente mediocre (habiendo vivido años en Nápoles esperaba algo más de un dueño que dícese Napolitano). En fin, una versión muy poco recomendable de lo que realmente puede ofrecer Barcelona en cuanto a gastronomía italiana. Locales como La bella Napoli o Pizza circus le dan mil vueltas, y por precios mucho más napolitanos.

Le digo que no, que no voy a coger bebida, que sólo quiero el vaso. No hay tu tía. No lo entiende. Después de hacer un gasto de 16 euros (debe ser el más caro de España), no puede darme un vaso de 5 cms. Hasta en los King auto te lo regalan con el hielo y una sonrisa incluida. VERGONZOSO. Claro que la dependienta en cuestión fue incapaz de explicarles a los que iban delante de mí que esa cola era "take away". Les decía "to bring". Aquí, vergüenza ajena.  Los pobres al final se marcharon dejando medio pedido atrás (pagado). A saber lo que le entendieron. MUY, MUY MAL.

reviews.excerpt:
It is a medium-small sized shopping center, built around the Carrefour supermarket. As for the shops, they are generally nice: several cloths and shoes dealer, a couple of bars and a few fast-food dealers, an electronics shop (Euronics), a bookstore, etc.
The supermarket is OK. One can find products of all sorts, e.g. cloths, sportsware, car parts, detergents, food... However, compared to homologous wide-surface supermarkets in France, this one stands on the rather smallish side, so certain items are missing or available only seasonally. Among food, fresh fish and cold cuts are available with a broad choice and good quality. Bakery sucks. Prices are OK overall. Nice discounts, usually offered through a customer-loyalty program, make this supermarked one of the cheapest in Pavia. 2016 saw the introduction of a single line: it smoothed queuing out a bit, except at peak times.
The parking lot was planned oversize: it is never packed. On the other hand, one-ways make driving rather confusing and labyrinthine.

Si no llega a ser porque era ya de noche y no se veía nada no nos hubiésemos acercado: la terraza es estupenda, pero el bar está mugriento (sólo hay fotos de la zona del comedor y no de la barra), huele a fritanga y en el baño hay una extraña tubería que hace ruidos inclasificables. 

Los camareros eran amables, pero caminaban muy lento y con los brazos caídos; además, parecía que había que encender una bengala para que se acercasen a la mesita.

reviews.excerpt:
Pleasantly surprised.

Stayed in the hotel Villa Oniria so thought to also try the restaurant.

Dishes are around 20-30 Euros maximum, however it came with 2 tapas and a pre-starter dish, then a pre-dessert dish and a post-dessert dish (6 in total!!!), combined with our starters, mains and desserts we definitely left with the feeling of value for money!

The restaurant had a nice ambience, certainly romantic enough as a special night for a couple.

Price-wise expect it to be around 50 euros /head before wine. Would heartily recommend you to try it!

reviews.excerpt:
DO NOT BOOK THIS HOTEL!!!!!

We were extremely disappointed to learn that this hotel appear to possibly be run by management which policy is to trick you out of as much money as possible. 
 
All staff seemed to be well versed in what to tell customers and appeared VERY used to receiving similar complaints as my own. 

The Story: 
We were told that our booking was not flexible when we asked to change our booking from 9th to 8th (or cancel) a few weeks prior to arrival (despite most hotels offering a total cancellation policy, even the day before arrival!)  In addition, we were told all family rooms were booked up and we needed to book two double rooms - at twice the cost of course, for the 8th.  We only booked this hotel as we arrived late and near the airport, but accidentally booked it for wrong date. It's located by motorways in the middle of nowhere so we didn't want to hang around more than a night. 

When we arrived late in the evening, the porter at the reception mentioned a sofa-bed that could be pulled out, but quickly withdrew his comments when we wanted to know more. 

The next day we moved to our family room that we booked originally for 9th, ONLY TO DISCOVER THAT THE FAMILY ROOM WAS IN FACT IDENTICAL TO THE FIRST ROOM THAT WE WERE TOLD WAS A DOUBLE ROOM, it just had the sofa-bed pulled out ready to sleep in rather than folded in.  I instantly went down to reception to raise this issue, and was very surprised at how the staff dealt with it.  

The chap at reception barely batted an eye lid. He said if i'm not happy with the room blah blah blah.  I reiterated that i wasn't complaining about the room, I was unhappy that we had been tricked into paying for TWO rooms for the first night, when the hotel was firstly obviously a) not fully booked as they had said and b) the family room and the double room is the same. The chap still gave me his well versed story (as he continued with his paper filing and stapling) about how the rooms may look identical but in fact weren't (but no matter how much i tried to get an explanation, he didn't elaborate on how!).  He appeared neither surprised of my comments or had any inclination of wanting to explain. To me, it seemed that they say this to customers every day all day. Eventually, he said 'anyway you're actually lucky because on the second night you're paying less'.  Either having no braincells whatsoever as I had fully explained why were have had to book the first night there in any event, or, as i suspect, had been told so say this as part of their versed reply. When I asked to see the manager, he pretended to do the act of walking into a back office, but lingered at the door and instead the girl next to him behind the reception appeared, repeating again that I was lucky because on my second night (that I didn't want if you remember) i paid less. All seeming a very well versed act.  She also said that the first room did NOT have a sofa bed just a sofa.  I told them that in fact the porter on duty on our first night had actually owned up to the fact that it did INDEED have a sofa bed, but the reply i got was the same rehearsed reply, and explanation which in fact didn't quite fit in with my particular unique circumstances, but i guess if you don't have a real explanation (being - we lied to you to get more money out of you) then you go with what you've been told to say.

reviews.excerpt:
Fuimos para hacer unas gafas de sol y al final salimos con un pack de 3 gafas, de las cuales unas eran de la oferta, sencillas. Otras, las de sol y las terceras unas gafas buenas con cristales antirreflejantes, bla bla bla.
Las gafas de sol tienen un defecto en uno de los cristales, como si le hubiera caído una gota de tinta. Es un fallo en la coloración. No molesta mucho, pero ahí está.
Las gafas "buenas" tuve que ir a cambiar uno de los cristales al poco de tenerlas. Se empezó a "pelar" la lente, probablemente la capa antirreflejante, mientras la otra lente estaba perfecta. Tenía pinta de ser defectuosa/baja calidad.
Las terceras gafas apenas me las he puesto, las de la oferta. Eran tan sencillas que no se les puede pedir mucho más. Ya sabíamos lo que comprábamos.

En cualquier caso, una característica que se daba en las tres gafas era que la persona que nos las vendió no tuvo en cuenta en ningún momento el tamaño de la cabeza de la persona que las iba a llevar, fabricando las 3 gafas en una talla pequeña, que hacía que se clavara en los laterales de la cabeza. Las 3 no se ajustaban. Ni una ni dos, las tres mal. Esto ha ocasionado que, tiempo después, me haya hecho unas gafas nuevas en una óptica "de verdad". Las gafas nuevas ajustan de forma perfecta, no se clavan en la cabeza y encima ahora veo bien. Con las de afflelou nunca llegué a ver correctamente. Tiempo después (2 meses) de dejar de llevar las dichosas gafas afflelou, todavía tengo marcadas en la cabeza la forma de las patillas de las anteriores gafas. Una verguenza.
reviews.author: Lorenzo de Diego

reviews.subj: Review from Juan Antonio Lara Alcalá
reviews.excerpt:
Cliente de muchos años, celebrando aniversarios y momentos importantes con ellos. Buena cocina y trato por el personal en general.
Una estrella, por que hoy se han estrellado: mucho que desear con el trato al cliente. 
Después de tantos años realizando cenas de empresa y muchas otras celebraciones alli, me encuentro ante la siguiente situacion; se realiza una reserva por teléfono, y se pregunta si se puede llevar una tarta de fuera, cuando nos responden que no hay problema y que la llevemos incluso antes para que así pueda ser una sorpresa. Una vez llegado el día, me presento con la tarta en el restaurante, y después de mostrarme un documento de "sanidad" que desconocía, me dicen que no puedo dejar la tarta allí. 
Una cosita señores, después de crear esta situación que habéis generado vosotros por no explicar a sus trabajadores las normas o bien por no escuchar a los clientes realmente cuando llaman, hay que dar soluciones, no buscar culpables y generar malestar. Se me ha tachado de querer hacer daño a un trabajador, que van a ir a mi negocio a poner una reclamación también y de otras cosas de las cuales me daría vergüenza decir a un cliente, no me habría importado comprar una tarta a ustedes mismos (si lo hubiera sabido se habría hecho así). Sé que la reclamación puesta no sirve para nada, pero hoy habéis perdido clientes.
Existen cursillos de atención al cliente muy baratitos e instructivos, os recomiendo que se le imparta al personal.

Hoy día muy decepcionado, no saben mediar con el cliente, trato nefasto por parte del personal que te recibe al entrar.
reviews.author: Juan Antonio Lara Alcalá

reviews.subj: Review from Luis Alfonso Baroja Pérez
reviews.excerpt: Como cualquier otro local de mercadona los precios de la marca blanca están muy ajustados para la calidad que ofrecen. El personal es simpático y por lo general no hay muchas colas ...y si las hay intentan abrir una caja lo antes posible. No le pongo 5 estrellas por que siempre se puede mejorar, el aparcamiento esta bastante retirado, por que cobran las bolsas (muy extendido a la mayoría de las cadenas) y por que la encargada me dijo que no podía sacar una foto a una crema hidratante... Sus razones tendría (me dijo algo pero no lo recuerdo) pero yo sólo quería cerciorarme que hacia el encargo correctamente. Lo dicho en general recomendable.

reviews.excerpt:
Pues lo de siempre en los establecimientos de cadena. Cosas ricas que supuestamente llevan café a precios desorbitados. 

Solo vengo aquí por dos motivos: 

- Si necesito escribir artículos o relatos fuera de distracciones de mi casa (tengo dos gatas y muchos juegos allí...) 
- Si el club vips me da billetes eurovips o promociones de cosas gratis o rebajadas para el Starbuck. 

Servicios limpios, personal agradable y mesas rápidamente recogidas. Este sitio tiene la ventaja de que está justo al lado de Alonso Martínez (sales y te caes en una de sus bocas de metro) y puedo venirme un rato antes de la hora a la que haya quedado en el centro y adelantar trabajo de escritura.

reviews.excerpt:
Cosmética: iluminador de ojos y cubreojeras de muy buena calidad.
Casa: amoníaco perfumado para lavadora que no rompe la ropa.
Cápsulas de lavadora muy potentes.
Suavizante lavadora con aroma persistente, y con muy poca dosis.
Bicarbonato para blanquear prendas y juntas de silicona en cocina y baño. 1kg a 1€. No lo venden en otro sitio ni más barato ni tanta cantidad. Muy útil si lo juntas con vinagre blanco para quitar manchas antiguas o ropa amarillenta.
Comida: Croquetas congeladas de jamón ibérico, bolsa de color negro, exquisitas.
Mozzarella fresca, anchoas, yogures con frutas, barquillos rellenos, tacos de jamón serrano, o jamón al corte de buena calidad.
Aceite para tostas con difusor, excelente idea y gran sabor.
Higiene: productos de celulosa para mujeres, más baratos, no de marcas blancas.
Pañuelos de papel tipo klinnex, marca propia, muy buenos y baratos. Suaves y con loción para las narices sensibles y los catarros o gripes.
Crema facial 24 gold en tarrina. Muy hidratante en todo el cuerpo. 2 €.
Aceite de Argán marca propia para el pelo, eficaz para las puntas abiertas o pelo castigado.

reviews.excerpt:
You must have 1 hour for domestic transit and 2 hours or more for international flight. Terminal 4 to 4s will take you more than half hour to get to your gate. If you flight is delay and you need to go to other terminal you'll miss your flight. We had to go out side to departure area to get new tickets because we miss our flight. And must go through security again. Very stressfully airport if you don't have enough time to catch your next flight.
After 1st experience, we change our return flight so we have 4 hours transit. 
If you have 4 hours of transit Good is shopping and delicious food.
reviews.author: Cris Tayza

reviews.excerpt: Worst airport in my whole long and rich travelling life ! In this "International" Airport, staff dont speak English (nor French) and they are proud of it, while addressed they scream in Spanish "no engless, no engless" !, utters insults in Spanish. If u have to pass several hours in this "International" Airport, better bring a comfortable chair because what they have is iron chairs for torture cells. If u want to go the toilet, be careful, the cleaning-woman will scream at u in Spanish !! Never ever I had such experience in an airport. They r so proud to be ignorant of the rest of the world, may be world should live without them; all the shops and business in the airport, they are not Spanish I guess ;-)))
reviews.author: tiash roy

reviews.excerpt: Be careful of Hertz Spain. Instead of the normal 500 to 700 Euro excess our rental came with a 14,000 Euro excess (worth more than the car itself). reviews.author: Joe Thuraisamy

reviews.excerpt: After a number of times I think this is one of the world's worst newest airports: does not hub well (poor design means not a simple connection) inconsistent security staff (liquids went unchecked yet another time a metal key was confiscated in case I broke glass with it!) and idiotic Iberia staff when it all goes wrong.

- reaching the airport from the city is very bad. I had to pay 30 euros for taxi

reviews.excerpt:
One of the better places in town for a quick lunch off the centre, in the piazza Bologna area. Full of young people and goodlooking students, as well as older intellectuals. Where can you have a good meal for just € 8? Sparkling water included. Good service by the friendly staff.
In an area full of history, build by the fascists in the thirties and in the sixties centre of young rebels. And the girls that frequent this place are very beautiful too!
And the music there is great. Keep your Shazam at hand. I heard my first sounds of Paolo Nutini here. I thought he was Italian but turned out as being Scottish. Long live Europe!

reviews.excerpt:
Hola. Hoy he estado en el 123 wok. Bueno la comida no ha estado mal....(tenia habré y mono de sushi) pero me ha costado 9.90€ ( por ese precio q más quiero) he entrado a las 12.45. Creo q a las 13.00 vale 7.95€ . No hubiera estado mal q m lo hubiesen comentado. 
Al grano. El arroz 3 delicias rico. El pollo plancha o sus variedades no estaban mal. La pasta un poco pasada para mi gusto. El sushi un poco correoso pero se podía comer, otros días estaba mejor. El camarero No me han dejado sentarme donde yo quería , osea en una mesa de 4 con cojin goma espuma más cómodo q las sillas. Eso es un 1 fallo (dado q no hay nadie solo 5 personas) si me dices q son las 15.00 y está lleno lo entiendo, pero cuando está vacío , no se , me parece ley del mínimo esfuerzo, y todo fijo que por no retirar papel de publicidad de encima de la mesa. 

Limpieza= necesita mejorar = ver foto churreton de resto de comida en la pared. (Me da corte decírselo al camarero mejor que lo vean publicado y saquen brillo al suelo y paredes)

Refresco barato de máquina de bolsa de glucosa (q sabe a agua y azúcar con burbujas).

Por suerte el suelo es de granito para evitar q se aprecie la mierda. Pero el mástil de la mesa estaba con restos de comida seca. Ver foto.

Por favor dueño del 123. Limpien las mesas no sólo por arriba si no por abajo también.

Lo mejor: las servilletas para limpiarme la boca después de potar . Bueno y la fruta fresca , piña cortada y melón y naranjas naturales muy saludables. Pero claro después de llenarme la panza de fritanganos baratos no m ha entrado postre

Lo peor: todo. 
Repetiré?  Nunca se sabe a lo mejor 1 dia paso por la puerta todo pedo y entro a cagar al wc.

Amigos y amigas, si queréis comer bien .... haceros en casa cualquier cosa que seguro q esta más rica q lo he comido yo hoy.

Le doy 2 estrellas por darle algo.

Ah y 2.75€ del parking del centro comercial príncipe pio.
reviews.author: G G

reviews.excerpt: Midsized shopping center that totally blew it! Could be much more and better if it had used its geographic location better. Great way to avoid the mid day heat in the summer. Only thing missing is a place to look at the view since all the stores look inwards towards center court. Needs an observation deck.

reviews.excerpt:
Great family hotel, fantastic family vacations.
Thanks for these great weeks!

Top service, always friendly and open-minded, very clean, excelent animation. Also a fantistic buffet at the poolside or during the dinner.

You have also great partners for example a diving school which delivers a great service for aldults and kids w/o to point to the important facts and also asking for a test (theroritical, oral and practical) before my son gets his junior scuba diver.

The combination of relaxing, adventure and family vacation is top.

Thanks you! We have spent the 2nd time in your hotel and I am sure that we will come again next year.

reviews.excerpt: Amazing through and through!!!!  It was perfect for our honeymoon.  Good variety of food, clean rooms and Marcell (activities coordinator) was very good!

reviews.excerpt: Our room (9524) was absolutely fantastic - as we were on the first floor we left the window open through the night to hear the sea as we fell asleep. We chose the privilege service and were very pleased with the additional choices available to us. Branded drinks, decent wine, mikes coffee bar incl, privilege check in, privilege lounge and great full waiter served restaurants offering a good menu, a fully stocked mini bar and nespresso machine etc etc. The hotel is in a good location too, offering a nice walk into playa Blanca harbour one way (35 mins) and a lighthouse the other (20 mins) It's so nice to stretch your legs and have great scenery at the same time. The service has been brilliant in all the restaurants and as it's self service in the privilege lounge we didn't have to wait for any drinks! We have completed a few surveys whilst we've been here suggesting a few minor tweaks, which proves they are always trying to make improvements based on customer feedback. I'm sure we'll return next year.
reviews.author: Janet Turner

reviews.excerpt: Lovely place. Been back there many times and still the most reliable holiday experience we've ever had. Being Lanzarote the weather is reliable year round. The staff are all very friendly and helpful, some are truly exceptional. Poolside can get busy but it's not hard to find a place to relax elsewhere. Privilege is worth the extra if you want to feel a bit special. There has been an obvious effort to improve maintenance and public spaces recently. Lots of new paint and floor tiles. WiFi used to be poor but had been improved and is now genuinely good. Occasionally something in the room wasn't perfect but it was always resolved with a smile. Buffet and a-la-carte food is good quality and there's plenty of it. Some a-la-carte dishes can have large amounts of meat and few vegetables, which is only great if that is your preference. Easy access to the coastal path allows for pleasant after-dinner walks past beaches, Playa Blanca town and beyond.

reviews.excerpt: really pretty touristy place but a bit overpriced for what it is in my opinion. the place couldve done with some more explaining about what it actually was i was visiting. great place to take aesthetic photos though
reviews.author: Marit de Goede

reviews.excerpt:
.

Now in very poor condition.  :-(  Very sad.

Yes, it used to be "Stunning", "Wonderful", "Just Beautiful", and all the other things that people say.

And it could be again.

But frankly at the moment it is none of these things because of the lack of basic maintenance.

Hundreds of people come here every day, so of course there is wear and tear. They should invest some of the entrance fee into getting it back up to standard.

Currently some of it is actually dangerous, with the main path in the large cave falling to pieces, a real tripping hazard. Safety barriers at the side of paths and stairways were often broken or missing.

And when you combine that with broken handrails . . . :-( Not good, folks.

And the Casa de los Volcanes - an exhibition centre as part of the Jameos complex - it too could do with a re-vamp.

A large amount of the interactive displays were not working, it was dirty and dusty, and actually out of date, with no mention whatsoever of recent volcanic activity in the Canaries. By recent I mean the quite severe volcanic activity in El Hierro in 2011. Surely in 5 years they could have managed to get something organised?

So I found it disappointing re-visiting it after nearly 20 years.
reviews.author: Jennifer Longhurst

reviews.excerpt: Totally agree with Jennifer - the place is outdated and soulless. Over priced and nothing much going on really! It kind of felt like we'd stumbled upon a rave the morning after, which I think would be a much better use of this place tbh!!
reviews.author: Mina Nishimura

reviews.excerpt: The idea for the place is great and unique. It is definitely a must-see. There is a different kind of beauty in every part of it. Seems lifeless, though. I wish there was more going on there.
reviews.author: Adam Michał Małecki

reviews.excerpt: Tempi di servizi lunghissimi (sabato a pranzo): innanzitutto bisogna comporre il proprio menù utilizzando un grosso schermo touch preceduto da file interminabili di persone, successivamente dovete pagare con una carta oppure recarvi alla cassa ed infine ritirare l'ordinazione quando il numero assegnatovi verrà chiamato. È un sistema che dovrebbe ridurre i tempi di attesa, ma secondo me non fa altro che aumentarli proprio per la non ottimale user experience dell'interfaccia per ordinare. La qualità è quella dei McDonald's italiani: rimane un fast food, ma senza dubbio migliore di quella dei ristoranti della catena sparsi per l'Europa.
